machining learning testing ground

To convert HGC gemc output into a text file, run it on jlab ifarm like

root -l -b -q 'analysis_hgc.C+("/volatile/halla/solid/sim/solid_gemc/cc_pro_JLAB_VERSION_1.3/pass1/cc_pro_SIDIS_He3_e_even_central_1.root","trigger",false,"single")'

The result is an output of text file called *_pixel.ml" 
each event starting a new line with content "event numberrrr"
then follow each photoelectron has a line with columns separated by tab as "pixel id"  "mother particle pid"   "mother track id"

pixel_id=16*64*sector+32*pixel_y+pixel_x
mother particle pid is 11 for electron, -11 for positron
mother track id is 1 for the initial particle, larger numbers for secondary particles

